10.5 Managing modules and application streams	

the yum module command is used to manage module properties
	yum module list - lists available module
	yum module provides httpd - searches the module that provides a specific package
	yum module info php - shows more info on a module
	yum module info --profile php - shows profules
	yum module list php - shows streams that are available
	yum module install php:7.1 or yum install @php:7.1 - installs the module and stream you selected. These commands are the same
	yum module install php:7.1/devel - installs a specific profile
	yum module install php:7.1 will install and enable a specific stream
	yum module install php:7.2 will update to the newer version and disable 7.1
	to update or downgrade packages froma  previous module stream that are not listed in profiles in the newest module update, use yum distro-sync
	
	
Module is a collection of packages that gives you everything you need for a specific used
stream is the update number
profile can be things such as installs for devs, users, or minimal installs